.TH BLUE "1" "June 2026" "blue v0.3.6-237283b-linux/amd64" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
blue \- blue - a fun programming language
.SH DESCRIPTION
blue is a tool for running blue source code
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
blue <command> [arguments]
.PP
The commands are:
.TP
lex
start the lexer repl or lex the given file (converts the file to tokens and prints)
.TP
parse
start the parser repl or parse the given file (converts the file to an inspectable AST without node names)
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-parser\-errors\fR
show all parser errors instead of stopping at the first one
.TP
bundle
bundle the given file into a go executable with the runtime included (bundle accepts a '\-d' flag for debugging)
(NOTE: currently non\-functional)
.TP
doc
print the help strings of all publicly accesible functions in the given filepath or module
.IP
note: the file/module will be compiled to gather all functions
.TP
vm
run the given string or file through the VM
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-parser\-errors\fR
show all parser errors instead of stopping at the first one
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-exec\fR
do not allow executing programs or scripts
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, e, eval
alternative ways to trigger the vm evaluation
.TP
compile
compiles the given string or file to bytecode
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-parser\-errors\fR
show all parser errors instead of stopping at the first one
.TP
help
prints this help message
.TP
version
prints the current version
.PP
The default behavior for no command/arguments will start an vm repl. (If given a file, the file will be evaluated with the vm)
.PP
Environment Variables:
.PP
BLUE_DISABLE_HTTP_SERVER_DEBUG   set to true to disable the gofiber http route path printing and message
.PP
BLUE_INSTALL_PATH                set to the path where the blue src is installed. ie. ~/.blue/src
.PP
NO_COLOR or BLUE_NO_COLOR        set to true (or any non empty string) to disable colored printing
.PP
PATH                             add blue to the path variable to access it anywhere. ie. ~/.blue/bin could be added to path with the blue exe inside of it
